ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: When I'm feeling mad, I can control my anger.
I hold my anger in.
I stay calm and keep my cool when I'm feeling mad.
I can pretend to be angry, even when I'm not.
I do things like slam doors when I'm mad.
I hide my anger.
I attack whatever it is that makes me very angry.
I get mad inside, but don't show it.
I can stop myself from losing my temper when I'm mad.
I say mean things to others when I'm mad.
I try to calmly deal with what is making me mad.
I'm afraid to show my anger.
Sometimes I feel angry, but I pretend not to be.
How often do you experience feeling mad each day?
Notes: 1 = Never; 2 = Hardly Ever; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Usually; 5 = Often
